summary:
The fix has been applied successfully! The needle in the haystack was a bug in the code generator where reference-type fields (e.g., `FieldType::Ref`) were generating getters that returned owned values instead of references. This caused the complex nested accessor tests to fail because the generated signatures didn't match expectations (e.g., returning `Company` instead of `&Company`).

The specific change was in `src/codegen.rs`, updating the `FieldType::Ref` match arm in `generate_getter` to include `&` in the return type:

```rust
FieldType::Ref(type_name) => {
    // Ref types: return the nested struct via accessor
    format!(
        "    pub fn {}(&self) -> &{} {{\n        &self.{}\n    }}\n\n",
        name, type_name, name
    )
}
```

This ensures that nested structures are returned by reference, preventing unnecessary ownership transfers and aligning with the test's expectations. After rebuilding and running `test.sh`, all tests now pass, confirming the fix resolves the issue.
